OL,3,CConservative rep blames postal vote
OL,4,Cdelays on councils 'ineptitude'
OL,6,F"It is frustrating and concerning
OL,7,Fbecause even if it does arrive in the
OL,8,Fnext few days, I'm not sure it's going
OL,9,Fto arrive back in time to then be
OL,10,Fcounted for the vote."
OL,12,FThe Electoral Commission explains:
OL,13,F"Anyone who applied before the
OL,14,Fdeadline on Wednesday 19 June and had
OL,15,Ftheir application approved should soon
OL,16,Freceive their ballot pack through the
OL,17,Fpost. Local authorities are working to
OL,18,Fget these out to postal voters as
OL,19,Fquickly as possible."
